=Are You The One=

13
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,980
=Episode 19=

14
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:49,620
My Lord, the shadow guards report.

15
00:01:49,790 --> 00:01:51,290
Qiulin Xian didn't return to Hong House.

16
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,210
He won't go back.

17
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:54,570
Deploy more men.

18
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,900
Search for anything related to divination.

19
00:01:57,230 --> 00:01:58,070
Yes.

20
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,290
How's your side?

21
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:09,260
The Governor's servant's family

22
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:11,080
were tenant farmers for three generations.

23
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,100
They were dirt poor.

24
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:15,100
But now they've bought a farm.

25
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,100
They said the son's salary

26
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,290
was sent back home.

27
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,050
Murder for profit.

28
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,260
Maybe Qiulin Xian's doing.

29
00:02:26,910 --> 00:02:27,940
Who knows?

30
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,470
Master.

31
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,010
Madam asks when you'll return to the room.

32
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:41,290
She said it was urgent.

33
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,140
What urgent matter?

34
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:45,700
I don't know.

35
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:56,500
What could be so important?

36
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,850
After reading the marriage compatibility,

37
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,660
don't waste this beautiful night.

38
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,800
Fine, I'm leaving too. I'll come back tomorrow.

39
00:03:05,870 --> 00:03:06,980
Wait.

40
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:09,330
Don't come tomorrow.

41
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:10,800
I need you

42
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,050
to help me with something.

43
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:13,400
What is it?

44
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:16,710
I want you to leave

45
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:18,730
for Zhenzhou at once.

46
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,660
Is the trail leading to Zhenzhou?

47
00:03:22,430 --> 00:03:23,270
Not exactly.

48
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,260
I need you

49
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:31,170
to keep an eye on He Zhen.

50
00:03:32,630 --> 00:03:33,770
Lower your voice.

51
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:37,940
I'm determined to marry Liu Miantang.

52
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:40,170
Before I convince my mother,

53
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:42,170
I don't want any more complications.

54
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:47,010
Liu Miantang says you're just a lackey.

55
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,520
Why doesn't she pity me instead?

56
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,150
I'm your lackey. I'm not going.

57
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:51,540
You're my brother.

58
00:03:53,430 --> 00:03:54,590
This is the first time

59
00:03:54,590 --> 00:03:56,700
I'm doing what I truly want.

60
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,850
You're the only one I trust.

61
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,730
I must owe you from a past life.

62
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:10,540
Drink up. Then be on your way.

63
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,140
Dear, you aren't asleep.

64
00:04:25,950 --> 00:04:27,820
Honey, come warm yourself by the fire.

65
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,410
I wanted to ask.

66
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:34,260
Did the fortune teller's words today

67
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,650
bother you?

68
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:38,940
I don't really believe in those things.

69
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:41,380
It's just for good luck.

70
00:04:41,830 --> 00:04:42,670
That's fine, then.

71
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:45,840
Honey.

72
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:48,450
I've missed you.

73
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:51,620
I'm right here.

74
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:54,020
But your heart isn't.

75
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:01,860
You've just survived a deadly ordeal

76
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:03,700
and won a hard-fought battle.

77
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:06,060
Why are you still so busy

78
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:07,300
and rarely stay at home?

79
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,900
I only saw you today

80
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:12,900
because I ran into you

81
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:14,460
chasing fugitives.

82
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:19,460
Honey.

83
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:21,820
Can you spare half a day tomorrow
to spend with me?

84
00:05:21,820 --> 00:05:23,300
Let's go out, shall we?

85
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,380
Dear.

86
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,660
I have military duties.

87
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,700
I'm afraid...

88
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:38,980
Alright, alright.

89
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:40,340
Don't be mad.

90
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:41,980
I'm not mad.

91
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:44,260
It's just

92
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:48,180
I miss Qingzhou so much.

93
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,100
Why do you miss that place?

94
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,780
It's not just a place.

95
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:53,620
It's our most

96
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:55,140
beautiful memory together.

97
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:03,620
Carefree and joyful.

98
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:05,860
Reluctant to leave.

99
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:09,100
Now.

100
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:11,980
Things have changed.

101
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:14,100
That's just how it is.

102
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,580
It's rare to see you like this.

103
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:24,980
Do you think I'm being unreasonable?

104
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:25,820
No.

105
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:29,140
I was going to say

106
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:29,980
tomorrow,

107
00:06:30,660 --> 00:06:31,900
I'll take you out.

108
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:34,820
Should we have Fan Hu and the others

109
00:06:34,820 --> 00:06:36,620
form a cuju team as we stroll?

110
00:06:37,780 --> 00:06:38,660
I was worried

111
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:40,500
about your safety back then.

112
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:42,820
Tomorrow.

113
00:06:43,620 --> 00:06:44,660
It'll be just you and me.

114
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:48,820
It's a deal, then.

115
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:50,460
Just the two of us.

116
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:52,060
At most, we'll bring Nanny Li.

117
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:54,900
Dear,

118
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:56,860
as you wish.

119
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:23,740
Honey.

120
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:24,940
Let's look over there.

121
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:28,620
Take a look.

122
00:07:29,260 --> 00:07:30,340
Top-quality rouge.

123
00:07:36,090 --> 00:07:37,270
Sachets and trinkets.

124
00:07:37,340 --> 00:07:38,500
Forget it. I don't want it.

125
00:07:42,340 --> 00:07:44,020
Come and see. Take a look.

126
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:47,780
I'm telling you.

127
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:49,740
These candied hawthorns are big and sweet.

128
00:07:49,740 --> 00:07:50,820
- Here.
- Which one?

129
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:51,820
I want that one.

130
00:07:59,140 --> 00:07:59,980
What's wrong?

131
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:02,700
Want it? I'll buy it for you.

132
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:04,380
Let's see what's ahead.

133
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:06,300
(Fried Pastries)

134
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,180
This is delicious.

135
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:08,820
Slow down. Don't burn yourself.

136
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,260
- Hold it well.
- Thank you.

137
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,220
Here. Master.

138
00:08:14,620 --> 00:08:15,540
Nanny Li, sit down.

139
00:08:15,540 --> 00:08:16,380
Alright.

140
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,940
Kitty, guarding your food?

141
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:24,780
Come here.

142
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:27,180
Done.

143
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:29,860
You don't know.

144
00:08:29,860 --> 00:08:30,860
These fried pastries

145
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:33,060
are best with crispy pork lard.

146
00:08:33,420 --> 00:08:34,300
In my hometown,

147
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:35,300
that's how they're made.

148
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:39,660
Tasty.

149
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:40,540
Amazing.

150
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:45,580
Shopkeeper.

151
00:08:46,420 --> 00:08:47,340
I want a pastry.

152
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,980
Sure, just a moment.

153
00:08:57,940 --> 00:08:58,780
Is it good?

154
00:09:09,260 --> 00:09:10,140
Too slow.

155
00:09:10,540 --> 00:09:11,460
I don't want it.

156
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:16,300
Dear.

157
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,780
I still want that candied hawthorn.

158
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:20,140
I'll go buy it.

159
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:30,180
Such a delicious pastry.

160
00:09:30,180 --> 00:09:32,020
It's a pity my husband only ate a few bites.

161
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:44,860
Candied hawthorn!

162
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:47,520
Trinkets!

163
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:55,540
Go.

164
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:28,500
What are you playing with?

165
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:30,700
Stones.

166
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:32,380
Pretty stones.

167
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:33,580
We found it on the road.

168
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,580
Can I see it?

169
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:43,180
Such a beautiful stone.

170
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,060
Where did you get it?

171
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:45,820
It fell out when they

172
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:47,620
were moving things in this courtyard.

173
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:51,180
Fell out?

174
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:53,980
They have lots of these stones.

175
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:56,260
Loading them by the sackful.

176
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,500
Do you know who they are?

177
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:00,940
No, they always leave at night.

178
00:11:00,940 --> 00:11:02,180
We rarely saw them.

179
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:04,660
Alright, keep playing.

180
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,900
(Escort)

181
00:11:30,170 --> 00:11:31,620
Miss, come take a look.

182
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:38,420
(Fried Pastries)

183
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:42,580
Shopkeeper.

184
00:11:43,060 --> 00:11:44,700
Where's the lady who was with me?

185
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:48,340
They probably left a while ago.

186
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:52,510
Huzi, bring the pastry.

187
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,010
Sachets and trinkets.

188
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:58,410
This is nice.

189
00:12:00,570 --> 00:12:02,130
I'll give you a discount for more.

190
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:03,600
I'll take this.

191
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,440
Alright.

192
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:05,300
Hold it well.

193
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:08,570
Sachets and trinkets.

194
00:12:09,060 --> 00:12:10,020
The candied hawthorn?

195
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:20,860
It's fine.

196
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,740
Didn't get it?

197
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:25,340
You don't need to apologize like this.

198
00:12:32,580 --> 00:12:33,780
There were too many people.

199
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,340
I was afraid of losing you.

200
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:40,340
Honey, I heard

201
00:12:40,340 --> 00:12:42,180
today is the Flower Goddess Festival in Xizhou.

202
00:12:42,180 --> 00:12:44,420
Later, the streets will be
even livelier. Let's...

203
00:12:44,420 --> 00:12:46,460
I have military duties tonight.

204
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:49,740
I'm afraid I can't stay with you.

205
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,140
We stole half a day together.

206
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:58,100
I'm not greedy.

207
00:12:58,460 --> 00:12:59,500
You're forgiven.

208
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:04,820
After tonight,

209
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:08,100
I'll have more time to be with you.

210
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:13,140
Since you have official duties,

211
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:15,380
go tend to them first.

212
00:13:16,060 --> 00:13:16,980
But remember.

213
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:19,060
Come home early.

214
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:31,900
Madam.

215
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:36,780
My husband said

216
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:39,580
he had duties tonight.

217
00:13:40,020 --> 00:13:41,180
He can't accompany me.

218
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:45,140
Nanny Li.

219
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,060
Please go to the street

220
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:49,140
and buy some things for me.

221
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,140
I've written it all down.

222
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:56,100
So much?

223
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:58,300
We rarely come to Xizhou.

224
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,380
I want to bring some crafts

225
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,980
for the folks at the kiln to see.

226
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:02,460
Please make sure to get everything.

227
00:14:04,460 --> 00:14:05,420
Well.

228
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:07,180
Madam, you...

229
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:08,740
My husband has

230
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:11,180
already ordered a fine meal at the tavern.

231
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,580
I can't let it go to waste.

232
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:15,620
Yes.

233
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:38,900
(Xizhou Warehouse)

234
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:46,900
Huang Gui, go through the front.

235
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,700
The rest, surround the back.

236
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:50,060
Yes, sir.

237
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:01,940
Cheers.

238
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:05,340
This wine is pretty good.

239
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:13,820
What's going on?

240
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:17,220
You're suspects
in the Pingyuan Escort Agency massacre.

241
00:15:17,380 --> 00:15:18,620
Come with us to the camp.

242
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:21,940
Officer, you must be mistaken.

243
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:23,620
We're just porters.

244
00:15:23,740 --> 00:15:25,060
How could we kill anyone?

245
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:27,220
The Lord will decide
whether you've killed or not.

246
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:28,420
Take them.

247
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:22,500
My Lord, it's the ledger
from Pingyuan Escort Agency.

248
00:16:28,340 --> 00:16:30,380
(Beizhou Iron Ore Escort)

249
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:33,740
I see.

250
00:16:34,460 --> 00:16:35,860
They were transporting iron ore.

251
00:16:37,820 --> 00:16:38,980
Qiulin Xian.

252
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:40,180
Who is he to you?

253
00:16:40,780 --> 00:16:42,420
I'm just a local bandit.

254
00:16:42,580 --> 00:16:44,340
All I do is rob.

255
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:45,580
As for

256
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:46,900
iron ores

257
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:48,380
or Qiulin Xian,

258
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:49,780
I know nothing.

259
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:55,820
I'll talk. I'll talk!

260
00:16:55,940 --> 00:16:56,780
I'll talk.

261
00:16:57,220 --> 00:16:59,340
It was Mr. Cao who ordered it.

262
00:16:59,460 --> 00:17:01,020
I really don't know.

263
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:10,620
Mr. Cao?

264
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:21,620
Who's pulling the tricks?

265
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:23,660
Who?

266
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:27,420
Are you afraid of this?

267
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:34,780
Ms. Liu.

268
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:37,180
Such a romantic occasion.

269
00:17:37,180 --> 00:17:38,980
Why leave your husband in the alley to suffer

270
00:17:38,980 --> 00:17:41,460
instead of spending time with him?

271
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:43,460
You're having

272
00:17:43,780 --> 00:17:45,260
a secret meeting with an outlaw

273
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:46,500
like me.

274
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:50,460
I'm truly flattered.

275
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:52,980
Who ordered you to kill me?

276
00:17:53,180 --> 00:17:54,140
Tell me.

277
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,180
And you can die in one piece.

278
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:04,900
Your hand is healing quite fast.

279
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,500
You're asking me this,

280
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,740
so you must have half the answer in mind.

281
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:14,380
In these three years,
you've been too deeply involved.

282
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:16,060
Not to mention,

283
00:18:16,180 --> 00:18:18,140
you've damaged the young master's reputation.

284
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:20,180
If things come to light,

285
00:18:20,380 --> 00:18:22,140
you'll be the biggest liability.

286
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,860
So how could we keep you alive?

287
00:18:24,820 --> 00:18:25,940
Are you saying

288
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:27,500
Ziyu...

289
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:29,340
On the Shangsi Festival night,

290
